 Artist\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Astro \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Popularity Award\n| {{nom}}\n|- \n| rowspan = \"2\"|[[32nd Golden Disc Awards|2018]]\n| Disc Bonsang\n| ''[[Dream Part.01]]''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Yeon-ji|script-title=ko:[32\ud68c \uace8\ub4e0] \ubd80\ubb38\ubcc4 \ud6c4\ubcf4\ubd80\ud130 \uc2ec\uc0ac\uae30\uc900\uae4c\uc9c0..\uace8\ub4e0\ub514\uc2a4\ud06c, \ud1ba\uc544\ubcf4\uae30|url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=22191966|website=Ilgan Sports|publisher=JTBC Plus|accessdate=December 13, 2017|language=ko|date=December 11, 2017}}</ref>\n| {{nom}} \n|-\n| Global Popularity Award\n| Astro<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\ud574\uc678 \uc2e4\uc2dc\uac04 \ud22c\ud45c|url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/goldendisc/kr/vote|website=Ilgan Sports|publisher=JTBC Plus|accessdate=December 13, 2017|language=ko|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20171213124018/http://isplus.live.joins.com/goldendisc/kr/vote|archivedate=December 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[34th Golden Disc Awards|2020]]\n| Disc Bonsang \n| ''[[All Light]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Most Popular Artist \n| Astro\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Male Performance Award\n| Astro<ref>{{cite web |title=[2020 \uace8\ub4e0\ub514\uc2a4\ud06c]\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, \uc74c\uc6d0+\uc74c\ubc18 \ub300\uc0c1 \ub3d9\uc2dc \uc11d\uad8c\u2026\"\uacf5\uc815\ud55c 2020\ub144 \uae30\ub300\"(\uc885\ud569) |trans-title=[2020 Golden Disc] Bulletproof Boy Scouts to Dominate Music + Music Records \"Fair 2020 expectations\" (general)|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=076&aid=0003516381|author=Yoo Jung-na|website=Sports Chosun |accessdate=January 5, 2020 |language=ko |date=January 5, 2020}}</ref> \n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[Melon Music Awards]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"45%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Recipient\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n| 2016\n| Best New Artist\n| Astro\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n===[[Mnet Asian Music Awards]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"45%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Recipient\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2016 Mnet Asian Music Awards|2016]]\n| [[Mnet Asian Music Award for Best New Artist (Solo or Group)|Best New Male Artist]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Astro\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n| [[Mnet Asian Music Award for Artist of the Year|HotelsCombined Artist of the Year]]\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[Seoul Music Awards]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"45%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Recipient\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2017\n| Best New Artist \n| rowspan=\"5\" | Astro\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Bonsang Award \n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Popularity Award \n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Hallyu Special Award\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| 2020\n| QQ Music Most Popular K-Pop Artist Award<ref>{{cite web |url=https://y.qq.com/m/act/sma/index.html |work=QQ Music |title=\u7b2c29\u5c4aSMA-QQ\u97f3\u4e50\u6700\u53d7\u6b22\u8fceK-POP ARTIST\u5956 |language=zh |accessdate=January 31, 2020|archive-date=January 31, 2020|archive-url=http://archive.today/2020.01.31-105902/https://y.qq.com/m/act/sma/index.html}}</ref>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[SBS Power FM]] [[Cultwo Show]] Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"45%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Recipient\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n|2016\n|Rookie of the Year<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BOd_acOBRDH/|title=Instagram photo by \ub450\uc2dc\ud0c8\ucd9c\uceec\ud22c\uc1fc \u2022 Dec 26, 2016 at 5:27am UTC|publisher=}}</ref>\n|Astro\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[Soribada Best K-Music Awards]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"45%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Recipient\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n|2019\n|Global Hot Trend Award <ref>[https://www.soompi.com/article/1347636wpp/winners-of-day-2-of-2019-soribada-best-k-music-awards Winners Of Day 2 Of 2019 Soribada Best K-Music Awards.] soompi. Retrieved August 23, 2019.</ref>\n|Astro\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=upper-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.fantagio.kr/artists/astro/}} on [[Fantagio]] {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Astro (South Korean band)}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:South Korean boy bands]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance music groups]]\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2016]]\n[[Category:2016 establishments in South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean boy band}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Astro\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = Astro at \"Dream Part. 01\" Showcase.png\n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Astro in May 2017. From left to right: Jinjin, Sanha, Eunwoo, MJ, Moonbin and Rocky\n| origin           = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre            = [[K-pop]]\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = [[Fantagio]]\n| website          = {{URL|http://www.fantagio.kr/musicians/\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c/}}\n| current_members  = *MJ\n*JinJin\n*[[Cha Eun-woo]]\n*[[Moon Bin]]\n*Rocky\n*Yoon San-ha\n}}\n'''Astro''' ({{Korean|\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c}}) is a South Korean [[boy band]] formed by [[Fantagio]] that debuted in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fantagio.kr/groups/|title=Fantagio Groups List|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> The group is composed of six members: MJ, [[Cha Eun-woo]], [[Moon Bin|Moonbin]], Jinjin, Rocky and Yoon Sanha.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://search.naver.com/search.naver?sm=mtb_pcv&where=nexearch&query=%EC%95%84%EC%8A%A4%ED%8A%B8%EB%A1%9C|title=Official Astro Naver Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> They debuted with the single \"Hide & Seek\" from their debut EP ''[[Spring Up]]'', and were subsequently named by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as one of the best new [[K-pop]] groups of 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Herman|first1=Tamar|title=10 Best New K-Pop Groups In 2016|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2016/7625235/best-k-pop-debuts-2016|accessdate=6 July 2017|agency=Billboard|date=21 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Pre-debut===\nThe members of Astro were known as iTeen Boys while training as part of Fantagio iTeen, a rookie talent development program under the management agency [[Fantagio]]. The group's name and members were announced in August 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Yoon|first=Gi-baek|script-title=ko:\ud310\ud0c0\uc9c0\uc624 \ub274 \ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9, \ud300\uba85 '\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c' \ud655\uc815|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=396&aid=0000335291|accessdate=2017-12-22|agency=Sports World|publisher=Sports World|date=2015-08-14|language=ko}}</ref> That month, they starred in a web drama series titled ''To Be Continued''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Elizabeth|first=Hailie|title=ASTRO Kick Off Debut Promotions With New Web Drama 'To Be Continued'|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/232419/astro-kpop-to-be-continued.htm|accessdate=2017-12-22|agency=KpopStarz|publisher=KpopStarz.com|date=2015-08-19}}</ref> The web drama featured the members as themselves, as well as [[Kim Sae-ron]], [[Seo Kang-joon]], and [[Hello Venus]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Seo Kang Jun to act alongside rookie boy group ASTRO and Kim Sae Ron in 'To Be Continued'|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/08/seo-kang-jun-to-act-alongside-rookie-boy-group-astro-and-kim-sae-ron-in-to-be-continued|accessdate=2017-12-22|agency=Allkpop|publisher=Allkpop|date=2015-08-17}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Astro starred in their own reality show, ''Astro OK! Ready'', which was aired on [[MBC Every1]] at 7PM KST.<ref>{{cite news|title=Just Before Their Debut, Astro To Star In A New Reality Show|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/just-before-their-debut-astro-to-star-in-a-new-reality-show/|accessdate=2017-12-22|agency=Officially Kmusic|publisher=Officially Kmusic|date=2016-01-19}}</ref>\n\n===2016: Debut with ''Spring Up'', ''Summer Vibes'' and ''Autumn Story''===\nAstro's debut extended play ''[[Spring Up]],'' was released on February 23, 2016, featuring title track \"Hide & Seek\".<ref name=\"spring up\">{{cite web|url=http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=619875|title=Spring Up|work=[[Naver]] Music|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref> The group held a debut showcase where they announced their official fan club name Aroha (an abbreviation for \"Astro hearts all fans\").<ref>{{cite news|title=Astro Announces Their Fandom Name At Their Debut Showcase!|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/astro-announces-their-fandom-name-at-their-debut-showcase/|accessdate=26 October 2016|agency=Officially Kmusic|publisher=Officially Kmusic|date=26 February 2016}}</ref> Within a week of its release, ''Spring Up'' reached #6 on the [[Billboard chart|Billboard World Albums Chart]] in the United States,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/world-albums/2016-03-12|title=World Albums|date=2016-03-12|work=[[Billboard chart|Billboard]]|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref> as well as #4 on the [[Gaon Music Chart]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week |title=Spring Up on Gaon Chart |work=Gaon Music Chart |publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association |language=ko}}</ref> On February 25, the group released the music video for \"Cat's Eye\", containing clips from their web series ''To Be Continued''.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/02/check-out-astros-talent-show-themed-mv-for-cats-eye |title= Check out ASTRO's talent-show-themed MV for 'Cat's Eye'! |work=Allkpop |date=25 February 2016|accessdate=June 30, 2016}}</ref> In March, 6 the group was the only Korean act invited to the LeTV Entertainment Awards in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/03/astro-is-exclusively-invited-to-letv-entertainment-awards-in-china|title=ASTRO is exclusively invited to 'Letv Entertainment Awards' in China!|work=Allkpop|date=2016-03-22|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\nTheir second extended play ''[[Summer Vibes]]'' was released on July 1 with the title track \"Breathless\", with a music video featuring former [[I.O.I]] member and current [[Weki Meki]] labelmate [[Choi Yoo-jung (singer)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/06/astro-are-breathless-in-full-mv|title=ASTRO are 'Breathless' in full MV!|publisher=Allkpop|date=2016-06-30|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref> The album peaked at #6 on the Billboard World Albums Chart and #21 on the [[Billboard chart|Billboard World Digital Songs Chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7438251/astro-summer-vibes-world-albums-breathless |title=ASTRO Earn 2nd Top 10 Entry on World Albums With 'Summer Vibes'|work=Billboard|date=2016-07-13|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\nAstro performed at [[Staples Center]] in Los Angeles on July 31 for [[KCON (music festival)|KCON 2016]].<ref name=\"kcl\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7378226/dean-astro-added-kcon-usa-lineup|title=DEAN, ASTRO Added to KCON USA Lineup|work=Billboard|date=2016-05-20|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref> They held their first solo concert on August 27\u201328 at the KEPCO Art Center in Seoul.<ref>{{cite news|last=Han|first=In-gu|script-title=ko:\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c, \ub370\ubdd4 5\uac1c\uc6d4\ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub2e8\ub3c5\ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uac1c\ucd5c|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=009&aid=0003770629|agency=\ub9e4\uc77c\uacbd\uc81c|publisher=\ub9e4\uc77c\uacbd\uc81c|date=2016-07-20|accessdate=2017-12-22|language=ko}}</ref> The group also held showcases in Japan, Indonesia, and Thailand throughout the months of October and November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kpopmap.com/astro-meet-international-fans-1st-asia-concert-tour/|title=ASTRO to Meet International Fans at 1st Asia Concert Tour|work=Kpopmap|date=2016-08-18|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/08/astro-to-hold-their-first-asia-showcase-in-thailand|title=ASTRO to hold their first Asia showcase in Thailand!|work=Allkpop|date=2016-08-03|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\nAstro's third extended play ''[[Autumn Story (EP)|Autumn Story]]'', was released on November 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/astro-confirms-november-comeback-reveals-upcoming-concept|title=ASTRO Looks Lovingly Sweet In Teaser Images For \"Autumn Story\"|work=Soompi|accessdate=31 October 2016}}</ref> The music video features labelmate Sei of [[Weki Meki]].\n\n=== 2017: ''Winter Dream'', ''Dream Part.01'', first tour and ''Dream Part.02''===\nOn February 22, 2017, Astro released ''Winter Dream'', featuring title track \"Should Have Held On To You (Again)\". Despite the album being the final piece to the groups seasonal album concept, it was not promoted on music shows.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/949349wpp/astro-beautiful-white-new-teasers-special-album-winter-dream|title=Update: ASTRO Shares Highlight Medley For \"Winter Dream\"|date=Feb 13, 2017|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref>\n\nOn May 29, Astro released their fourth extended play ''[[Dream Part.01]]'', featuring title track \"Baby\".<ref>{{cite news|title=ASTRO bring fans into their store with \"Baby\"|url=http://www.onestopkpop.com/astro-bring-fans-into-their-store-with-baby/|accessdate=2017-12-22|work=One Stop K-Pop|date=2017-05-29}}</ref> The group held their first tour, titled \"The 1st ASTROAD\", from July 15\u2013August 29, with dates in Seoul, Osaka, and Tokyo.<ref>{{cite news|title=ASTRO to hold first ever solo concert in July|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/05/astro-to-hold-first-ever-solo-concert-in-july|accessdate=2017-12-22|work=Allkpop|date=2017-05-29}}</ref>\n\nOn November 1, Astro released their fifth extended play ''Dream Part.02'' featuring the title track \"Crazy Sexy Cool\"''.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8022233/astro-crazy-sexy-love-video-dream-pt-02-ep|title=Astro Returns With Smooth New 'Crazy Sexy Cool' Video|work=Billboard|date=2017-01-11|accessdate=2017-12-22}}</ref> On January 10, 2018, the group released a limited edition of their album ''Dream Part.02 'Wish''' version which sold out all 10,000 copies in pre-orders alone. The special album contains a poem by member Eunwoo, a hidden 'thanks to', and polaroid photos which the members took themselves.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/01/astro-sell-out-all-10000-copies-of-their-limited-version-dream-part02|title=ASTRO sell out all 10,000 copies of their limited version 'Dream Part.02' {{!}} allkpop.com|work=Allkpop|access-date=2018-01-10}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018: Global Fanmeeting Tour, ''Rise Up,'' and Group Hiatus===\nThroughout February and March 2018, Astro embarked on a fan meeting world tour visiting cities in countries such as the United States, Canada, South Korea, Japan, and Thailand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpopmap.com/2018-astro-global-fan-meeting-japan-thailand-dates/|title=2018 ASTRO Global Fan Meeting - Japan & Thailand Dates \u2022 Kpopmap|date=2018-02-28|website=Kpopmap|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref>\n\nOn July 24, 2018, Astro released ''Rise Up'' featuring title track \"Always You\". The album was not promoted on music programs due to internal issues at their label, Fantagio.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8482591/astro-k-pop-boy-band-talks-always-you-single-hiatus|title=K-Pop Boy Band Astro Talks 'Always You' Single, Artistry & Hiatus|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Despite not being able to promote in their home country the group toured cities such as Nagoya, Osaka, and Tokyo in their \"ASTROAD II in Japan\" tour throughout the month of August, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpopmap.com/astro-to-hold-astroad-ii-in-japan-this-summer/|title=ASTRO To Hold \"ASTROAD II In Japan\" This Summer \u2022 Kpopmap|date=2018-06-22|website=Kpopmap|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019: ''All Light,'' ''Venus,'' ''Blue Flame,'' and Moon Bin's Hiatus===\nOn January 16, 2019, they released their first full-length album, the first album release in general following their 8 month period hiatus, ''[[All Light]].'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8493899/astro-all-night-video|title=Astro Spends 'All Night' Among the Flowers in New Video: Watch|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> To further promote their first full-length album the group announced \"The 2nd ASTROAD Tour\", which included cities across Asia and North America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1295759wpp/astro-announces-dates-locations-2nd-world-tour|title=ASTRO Announces Dates + Locations For 2nd World Tour|date=Jan 21, 2019|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> On January 21, the label Fantagio announced four US shows following their 2nd Tapei Tour, to conclude with further tour dates in Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8494287/k-pop-boy-band-astro-world-tour-north-america-dates|title=K-Pop Boy Band ASTRO Set World Tour|date=January 22, 2019|website=Billboard|language=en|access-date=January 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 29, Astro gained their first music show award during promotions for their release \u201cAll Night\" on the SBS MTV music program [[The Show (South Korean TV series)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1300100wpp/watch-astro-tears-up-as-they-receive-1st-ever-win-on-the-show-with-all-night-performances-by-wjsn-roh-tae-hyun-and-more|title=Watch: ASTRO Tears Up As They Receive 1st Ever Win On \u201cThe Show\u201d With \u201cAll Night\u201d; Performances By WJSN, Roh Tae Hyun, And More|date=January 29, 2019|work=Soompi|language=en-US|access-date=January 29, 2019}}</ref>. \n\nOn April 3, Astro released their Japan debut EP, ''Venus'' featuring three original Japanese tracks along with three Japanese versions of their Korean singles \"Baby\", \"Always You\", and \"All Night\". The album garnered a successful debut, debuting #2 on the daily album chart of Japan's largest music site [[Oricon]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1315021wpp/astro-makes-successful-debut-in-japan-as-venus-grabs-no-2-on-oricons-daily-album-chart|title=ASTRO Makes Successful Debut In Japan As \"Venus\" Grabs No. 2 On Oricon\u2019s Daily Album Chart|date=Apr 4, 2019|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn November 12, Fantagio Music announced that Astro's member Moonbin would be going on a hiatus to recover from health issues and focus on his treatment<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://koogle.tv/media/news/astros-moonbin-to-take-break-due-to-health-issues/|title=ASTRO's Moonbin to take break due to health issues!|last=|first=|date=November 12, 2019|work=KoogleTV|access-date=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 20, Astro released their sixth extended play ''Blue Flame''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/now/article/609/0000198107|title=\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c \uce21 \u201c11\uc6d4 20\uc77c \ubbf8\ub2c8 6\uc9d1 \ucef4\ubc31, \uc0c9\ub2e4\ub978 \ubaa8\uc2b5 \ubcf4\uc5ec\uc904\uac83\u201d(\uacf5\uc2dd)|date=2019-11-05|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref> Moonbin focused on recovery from physical health concerns, allowing him to take a break from group promotions as parts were re-distributed temporarily to other members. Despite this, he participated in the album and appeared in the music video for Blue Flame.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1365201wpp/astros-moonbin-to-take-hiatus-due-to-health-concerns|title=ASTRO\u2019s Moonbin To Take Hiatus Due To Health Concerns|last=|first=|date=November 12, 2019|work=Soompi|access-date=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2020: ''One&Only'' ===\nOn March 13, Astro released special single album One&Only for their 4th anniversary debut.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/468/0000629631|title=\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c, \uc624\ub298(23\uc77c) \ub370\ubdd4 4\uc8fc\ub144 \uae30\ub150 \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc2f1\uae00 'ONE&ONLY' \ubc1c\ub9e4|date=2020-02-23|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n*MJ ({{Korean|hangul=\uc5e0\uc81c\uc774}})\n*JinJin ({{Korean|hangul=\uc9c4\uc9c4}})\n*[[Cha Eun-woo]] ({{Korean|hangul=\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0}})\n*Moon Bin ({{Korean|hangul=\ubb38\ube48}})\n*Rocky ({{Korean|hangul=\ub77c\ud0a4}})\n*Yoon San-ha ({{Korean|hangul=\uc724\uc0b0\ud558}})\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected details and chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\"|Title\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Details\n!colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\"|[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=03&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=All Light \u2013 Week 3, 2019|website=[[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon Chart]]|language=ko|accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\"|[[Oricon Albums Chart|JPN]]<br><ref name=\"All Light JPN\">{{cite web |url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2019-02-25/p/2/ |script-title=ja:\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2019\u5e7402\u670811\u65e5\uff5e2019\u5e7402\u670817\u65e5 |trans-title=CD album weekly ranking from February 11, 2019 to February 17, 2019 |publisher=Oricon |accessdate=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\"|[[Billboard charts#Albums|US<br>{{small|World}}]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/astro/chart-history/world-albums|title=Astro Chart History: World Albums|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[All Light]]''\n|\n*Released: January 16, 2019 {{small|(KOR)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/01/732_261553.html|title=ASTRO to release first full-length album on Jan. 16, but bumpy road ahead|work=[[The Korea Times]]|last=Dong|first=Sun-hwa|date=January 6, 2019|accessdate=January 9, 2019}}</ref>\n*Label: [[Fantagio#Fantagio Music|Fantagio Music]]\n*Formats: [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|download]], [[streaming media|streaming]]\n| 1 || 11 || 6\n|\n* KOR: 127,472<ref name=\"gaonyear2019\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=2019&hitYear=2019&termGbn=year|title=2019\ub144 Album Chart|trans-title=2019 Album Chart|website=Gaon Music Chart|accessdate=January 10, 2020|language=ko}}</ref>\n* JPN: 1,185<ref name=\"All Light JPN\"/>\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected chart positions and sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Details\n! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" |Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" |Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\" |[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>Gaon Weekly Album Chart\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=Spring Up}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=31&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=Summer