{"title_page": "Cha Eun-woo", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer, actor, and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Cha Eun-woo\n| image              = 170924 \ud478\ub4dc\ud2b8\ub7ed\uc774\ubca4\ud2b8.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Cha in 2017\n| native_name        = \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0\n| native_name_lang   = ko-Hang\n| birth_name         = Lee Dong-min\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1997|3|30}}\n| birth_place        = [[Gunpo]], [[Gyeonggi Province]], South Korea\n| education       = [[Sungkyunkwan University]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|actor|model}}\n| height             = {{height|cm=183}}<ref>{{cite news |title=\ucd5c\uc560\ub294 \ucd5c\uc560\uace0, \uc740\uc6b0\ub294 \uc740\uc6b0\ub2e4 |url=http://www.edujin.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=20862 |work=\uc5d0\ub4c0\uc9c4 \uc778\ud130\ub137 \uad50\uc721\uc2e0\ubb38 |date=November 30, 2018 |language=ko}}</ref>\n| othername          = Cha Eun-woo\n| alma_mater      = [[Hanlim Multi Art School]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer   \n| genre           = [[K-pop]]\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[Fantagio]]\n| associated_acts = [[Astro (South Korean band)|Astro]]\n}}\n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n| hangul    = {{linktext|\uc774|\ub3d9|\ubbfc}}\n| hanja     = {{linktext|\u674e|\u77b3|\u65fc}}\n| rr        = I Dong-min\n| mr        = Yi Tongmin\n| hangulstage    =  {{linktext|\ucc28|\uc740|\uc6b0}}\n| hanjastage     =  {{linktext|\u8eca|\u9280|\u512a}}\n| rrstage = Cha Eun-u\n| mrstage = Ch'a \u016cnu\n}}}}\n\n'''Lee Dong-min''' ({{korean|\uc774\ub3d9\ubbfc|\u8eca\u9280\u512a}}; born {{birth date|1997|03|30}}), professionally known as '''Cha Eun-woo ''' ({{Korean|labels=no|\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0}}), is a South Korean singer, actor, and model under the label of Fantagio. He is a member of the South Korean boy group [[Astro (South Korean band)|Astro]].\n\n== Early life ==\nCha Eun-woo was born on March 30, 1997,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fantagio.kr/artists/cha-eun-woo/profile/|script-title=ko:\ud310\ud0c0\uc9c0\uc624|website=Fantaigo|language=ko-KR|access-date=May 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180525230533/http://www.fantagio.kr/artists/cha-eun-woo/profile/|archive-date=May 25, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> in [[Gunpo]], [[Gyeonggi Province]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/688939 |script-title=ko:[My Name] \uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c (2) \uc724\uc0b0\ud558 \uc9c4\uc9c4 \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0|date=September 23, 2015|website=TenAsia|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nCha attended Suri Middle School, then Suri High School. He graduated from [[Hanlim Multi Art School]] in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=179625 |script-title=ko:[HD\ud3ec\ud1a0] \uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c(ASTRO) \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, \u2018\ud48b\ud48b\ud55c \ub208\uc6c3\uc74c\u2019(\ud55c\ub9bc\uc5f0\uc608\uc608\uc220 \uace0\ub4f1\ud559\uad50 \uc878\uc5c5\uc2dd)|date=February 15, 2016|website=Top Star News|language=ko}}</ref> He is currently attending [[Sungkyunkwan University]], majoring in performing arts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/music/now/read?oid=112&aid=0002850905 |script-title=ko:\"\ud6c8\ub0a8 \uc120\ubc30\uc758 \uc815\uc11d\" \uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, \ucea0\ud37c\uc2a4\uc5d0 '\ub9cc\ucc22\ub0a8'\uc774 \ub5b4\ub2e4|date=September 23, 2016|website=Herald Corporation|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:170602 Astro 02.jpg|thumb|upright|Cha eun woo going to ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'', 2017]]\n=== 2013\u201315: Career beginnings ===\nCha eunwoo debuted as an actor with a minor role in the film ''[[My Brilliant Life]]''.<ref name=brillant>{{cite web|url=http://www.thebk.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=171492 |script-title=ko:'\ub450\uadfc\ub450\uadfc \ub0b4\uc778\uc0dd' \uc2e0\uc608 \ubc30\uc6b0 \uc774\ub3d9\ubbfc, \uc0e4\ub77c\uc0e4\ub77c\uac00 \ucc1c!|date=December 11, 2014|website=The BK|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, Cha eunwoo along with the other members of his group participated in the web-drama ''[[To Be Continued (TV series)|To Be Continued]]''.<ref name=continue>{{cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=1439876997963256017 |script-title=ko:[TD\ud3ec\ud1a0] \uc6f9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud22c \ube44 \ucee8\ud2f0\ub274\ub4dc' \ucd9c\uc5f0\uc9c4 \ub2e4\ud568\uaed8 \ud654\uc774\ud305|date=August 18, 2015|website=TV Daily|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Debut with Astro, solo activities and rising popularity ===\n{{Main|Astro (South Korean band)}} Astro debuted on February 23, 2016 with the mini album ''[[Spring Up]]''. In August, Cha eunwoo participated in the Chuseok special variety show, ''Replies That Make Us Flutter''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/1406_201609160930017936 |script-title=ko:\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0\u00b7\ubb38\ube48 \ud45c \u2018\uc6b0\uc124\ub9ac\u2019\u2026\uc608\ub2a5\uc778\ub370 \uc65c \uc124\ub808\uc9c0?|date=September 16, 2016|website=YTN|language=ko}}</ref> In September, he participated in another Chuseok pilot program, ''Boomshakalaka''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000646305 |script-title=ko:'\ubd90\uc0e4\uce74\ub77c\uce74', \uae40\uc218\ub85c\u00b7\uc774\uc218\uadfc\u00b7\uc774\uae30\uad11\u00b7\ud558\ud718\ub3d9 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u202615\uc77c \ucd94\uc11d\ubc29\uc1a1|date=September 2, 2016|website=Xports News|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nCha eunwoo was announced as the MC of the show ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' alongside [[Kim Sae-ron]] and [[Lee Soo-min (actress, born 2001)|Lee Soo-min]], which he hosted from 2016 to 2018.<ref name=show>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201801281014353377724_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Cha Eun-woo talks about leaving \u2018Music Core\u2019|date=January 28, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> The same year, he starred in the web drama ''My Romantic Some Recipe''.<ref name=romantic>{{cite web|url=http://biz.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=20161115000644 |script-title=ko:\ub18d\uc2dd\ud488\ubd80, \uc300 \uc18c\ube44 \ucd09\uc9c4 \uc6f9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 \u2018\ub9c8\uc774 \ub85c\ub9e8\ud2f1 \uc378 \ub808\uc2dc\ud53c\u2019 \uacf5\uac1c\u202615\uc77c \ub124\uc774\ubc84 TV\uce90\uc2a4\ud2b8 \uccab\ubc29|date=November 15, 2016|website=Herald Corporation|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Cha eunwoo was cast in the KBS2 drama ''[[Hit the Top]]''.<ref name=hit>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20170324n10849?mid=n0107 |script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\uc5bc\uad74 \ucc9c\uc7ac' \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, \uc720\ud638\uc9c4PD '\ucd5c\uace0\uc758 \ud55c\ubc29' \ud569\ub958|date=March 24, 2017|website=Nate|language=ko}}</ref> The same year, he starred in the web drama ''[[Sweet Revenge (TV series)|Sweet Revenge]]''.<ref name=revenge>{{cite web|url=http://hankookilbo.com/v/0cd62ce3dc7e5f1648f771916f6ce8eb |script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uae40\ud5a5\uae30-\uae40\ud658\ud76c-\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, \uc6f9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ubcf5\uc218\ub178\ud2b8' \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026TV \ubc29\uc601\ub3c4 \uc720\ub825|date=July 21, 2017|website=Hankook Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Cha eunwoo starred in the web drama ''[[Top Management (TV series)|Top Management]]''.<ref name=top>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201810291647145064430_2|title=Cha Eun-woo to star in YouTube Original show \u2018Top Management\u2019|date=October 29, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> The same year, Cha eunwoo was cast in the JTBC romantic comedy series ''[[Gangnam Beauty]]'', his first leading role on television.<ref name=id>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201807261458584397939_2|title=Cha Eun-woo thankful for handsome role in \u2018My ID is Gangnam Beauty\u2019|date=July 26, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003262555 |script-title=ko:\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]'\uc544\uc774\ub514\ub294 \uac15\ub0a8\ubbf8\uc778' \uc784\uc218\ud5a5X\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815\u2026'\uc2f1\ud06c\ub85c\uc728 100%' \uc870\ud569|date=May 28, 2018|website=Naver|publisher=Sports Chosun|language=ko}}</ref> Cha eunwoo saw a rise in popularity after the series aired,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201808191650568520011_2|title=Cha Eun-woo is having a breakthrough year|date=August 19, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2018/08/682_253426.html|title=ASTRO's Cha Eun-woo hot in 'Gangnam Beauty'|date=August 7, 2018|website=The Korea Times}}</ref> and was included in GQ Korea's \u2018Men of the Year\u2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201811231743519806947_2|title=Cha Eun-woo makes GQ Korea\u2019s \u2018Men of the Year\u2019|date=November 23, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Cha eunwoo starred in the historical drama ''[[Rookie Historian Goo Hae-ryung]]'' alongside [[Shin Se-kyung]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201903041003676921&ext=na|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] \ucc28\uc740\uc6b0, MBC '\uc2e0\uc785\uc0ac\uad00 \uad6c\ud574\ub839' \ud655\uc815\u2026\ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \uc9c0\uc0c1\ud30c \uc8fc\uc5f0|date=March 4, 2019|website=My Daily|author=Lee Seung-rak}}</ref> In 2019 MBC Drama awards, Cha Eun-woo won Excellence Award for an Actor and Best Couple Award with [[Shin Se-kyung|Shin Se-Kyung]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1374425wpp/winners-of-the-2019-mbc-drama-awards|title=Winners Of The 2019 MBC Drama Awards|date=1577720742|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nOn July 2019, it was announced the Cha Eun-woo will be having his first fan meeting across Asia titled, \"Just One 10 Minute\" in October.  In December 2019, Cha Eun-woo was announced as a cast member of the new variety show, ''[[Handsome Tigers]]'', alongside [[Joy (singer)|Joy]], [[Lee Sang-yoon]], [[Yoo Seon-ho]], and [[Seo Jang-hoon]].<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111270703|title=\uc11c\uc7a5\ud6c8, \ub18d\uad6c\uc608\ub2a5 \uc9c1\uc811 \ub860\uce6d..\uc774\uc0c1\uc724\u00b7\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0\u00b7\uae40\uc2b9\ud604\u00b7\uc720\uc120\ud638 \ub4f1 \ud655\uc815 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|last=OSEN|date=December 2, 2019|website=mosen.mt.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref> In the K-pop Radar Year-End Chart, Cha Eun-woo was named as \"2019 Hot Instagrammer - Male\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/112/0003243731|title=\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, 2019\ub144 \ucf00\uc774\ud31d \ub808\uc774\ub354 \uc120\uc815 \ubba4\ube44 \uc870\ud68c\uc218 \ucd5c\ub300 \ubc43\uc9c0 \ud68d\ub4dd\u2025\uc6d4\ub4dc\ud074\ub798\uc2a4 \uc131\uc801|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Astro (South Korean band)}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album \n! Notes\n! Ref. \n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2018\n| \"Rainbow Falling\"\n| ''[[Gangnam Beauty]] OST''\n| \n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1004915081|title=[SBS Star] ASTRO Cha Eun-woo to Release Solo Track for His Recent Drama|date=August 31, 2018|website=SBS News}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Get Myself With You\"\n|rowspan=4|''S.O.U.L''\n|rowspan=4|as part of S.O.U.L \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2018/10/682_256378.html|title=Rising actors, singers collaborate for new band S.O.U.L|date=October 3, 2018|website=The Korea Times}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Gravity\"\n| rowspan=3|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003327133 |script-title=ko:'\ud0d1\ub9e4\ub2c8\uc9c0\uba3c\ud2b8' \uc548\ud6a8\uc12dX\ucc28\uc740\uc6b0X\uc815\uc720\