{"title_page": "Results of the 1924 Swedish general election", "text_new": "'''[[Sweden]]''' held a [[1924 Swedish general election|general election]] around 19 September 1924.<ref name=SCB>{{cite web|url=http://share.scb.se/ov9993/data/historisk%20statistik/SOS%201911-%2FValstatistiken%2FRiksdagsmannavalen%20(SOS)%201909-1968%2FValstatistik-Riksdagsmannavalen-1922-1923-1924.pdf|title=Riksdagsmannavalen \u00e5ren 1922-1924 av Kungl. Statistiska centralbyr\u00e5n - Valstatistik-Riksdagsmannavalen-1922-1923-1924.pdf|language=sv|publisher=[[Statistiska Centralbyr\u00e5n|SCB]]|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & St\u00f6ver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1858 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> This was the second election under [[universal suffrage]]. In spite of a majority for the non-socialist parties, [[Social Democratic Party (Sweden)|Social Democrat]] [[Hjalmar Branting]] was able to form a government, although his successor eventually saw the government fall and being replace by a right-leaning [[Moderate Party (Sweden)|Electoral League]] government.\n\n==Results==\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:right\n!Party\n!Votes\n!%\n!Seats\n!+/\u2013\n|-\n|align=left|[[Swedish Social Democratic Party|Social Democratic Party]]||725,407||41.1||104||+11\n|-\n|align=left|[[Moderate Party|General Electoral League]]||461,257||26.1||65||+3\n|-\n|align=left|[[Free-minded National Association]]||228,913||13.0||29||\u201312\n|-\n|align=left|[[Centre Party (Sweden)|Farmers' League]]||190,396||10.8||23||+2\n|-\n|align=left|[[Liberal Party of Sweden]]||69,627||3.9||4||New\n|-\n|align=left|[[Left Party (Sweden)|Communist Party]]||63,601||3.6||4||\u20133\n|-\n|align=left|[[Communist Party of Sweden (1924)|Communist Party (H\u00f6glund Tendency)]]||26,301||1.5||1||New\n|-\n|align=left|Other parties||84||0.0||0||0\n|-\n|align=left|Invalid/blank votes||5,473||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013\n|-\n|align=left|Valid votes||1,765,586||\u2013