gory:21st-century British women writers]]\n[[Category:British medical writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julia_Newton"}
{"title_page": "Robby Naish", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{No footnotes|date=September 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=September 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| honorific_prefix     = \n| name                 = Robby Naish\n| honorific_suffix     = \n| image                = RN Profile 2.jpg\n| image_size           = <!-- only when absolutely necessary -->\n| alt                  = \n| caption              = \n| headercolor          = \n| textcolor            = <!-- Personal information -->\n| native_name          = \n| native_name_lang     = \n| birth_name           = <!-- if different than name -->\n| full_name            = Robert Staunton Naish <!-- if different than name/birth_name -->\n| nickname             = \n| nationality          = \n| national_team        = <!-- only for the country represented in international competition -->\n| ethnicity            = \n| citizenship          = \n| birth_date           = {{birth_date and age|1963|04|23}}\n| birth_place          = [[La Jolla, California]]\n| death_date           = <!-- {{death date and age|death year|death month|death day|birth year|birth month|birth day}} -->\n| death_place          = \n| resting_place        = \n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| monuments            = \n| residence            = \n| hometown             = \n| education            = \n| alma_mater           = \n| occupation           = Athlete\n| years_active         = 1974-Present\n| employer             = \n| agent                = \n| height               = 5\u201910\u201d<!-- X cm, X m, or X ft Y in (automatic conversion) plus optional year and reference -->\n| weight               = 175 lbs<!-- X kg, X lb, or X st Y lb (automatic conversion) plus optional year and reference -->\n| spouse               = Bitsy Kelley (m. 1981, div. 1987), Kathryn Lipp (m. 1991; div. 2019)\n| life_partner         = \n| other_interests      = \n| website              = {{url|www.naish.com}}\n| module               = <!-- Sport -->\n| country              = \n| sport                = Windsurfing, Kiteboarding, Stand-up Paddling, Foiling, Wing-Surfing\n| position             = \n| disability           = \n| disability_class     = \n| weight_class         = \n| weight_class_type    = \n| rank                 = \n| event                = \n| event_type           = \n| universityteam       = \n| collegeteam          = \n| league               = \n| league_type          = \n| club                 = \n| team                 = \n| turnedpro            = \n| turnedpro_type       = \n| partner              = \n| former_partner       = \n| coach                = \n| retired              = \n| coaching             = \n| module2              = \n<!-- Achievements and titles -->\n| worlds               = \n| regionals            = \n| nationals            = \n| olympics             = \n| paralympics          = \n| commonwealth         = \n| highestranking       = \n| pb                   = <!-- Medal record -->\n| show-medals          = \n| medaltemplates       = \n| medaltemplates-title = \n| module3              = \n}}\n[[File:RN La Perouse 1.jpg|thumb|Robby Naish, La Perouse Bay, Maui, Hawaii 9-8-2019]]\n[[File:RN La Perouse 2.jpg|thumb|Robby Naish, Windsurfing, Aerial, La Perouse Bay, Maui, Hawaii, 9-8-2019]]\n\n'''Robert Staunton Naish''' (born April 23, 1963 in [[La Jolla, San Diego, California]]) is an American athlete and entrepreneur who has won 23 World Championship [[Windsurfing]] titles.  He is also considered a pioneer of [[kiteboarding]] and stand-up [[paddleboarding]] (SUP). \n\nIn 1976, Naish won his first world championship in windsurfing at age 13 in the [[Bahamas]]. Since then, he has been featured in films, videos, news reports, and articles. In 1996, Naish founded Naish Sails Hawaii, which manufactures and sells [[sailboards]], sails, kitesurfing equipment, stand up paddle boards and paddles, [[hydrofoils]], foil boards, and wing-surfers.\n\n===== Sponsors =====\n* [[Red Bull]]\n* [[Quiksilver]]\n\n===== Awards =====\n* 1976 Windsurf World Champion\n* 24-times Windsurfing World Champion\n* 1998 Kiteboarding Slalom World Champion\n* 1999 Kiteboarding Slalom and Jumping World Champion\n* 2000 \u201cLifetime Achievement Award\u201d and \u201cKiteboarder of the Year\u201d at NEA International Sports Awards Munich, Germany\n* 2000 \u201cBoarder of the Millennium\u201d at the French Boarder Awards\n* 2002 PWA Hall of Fame Induction\n* 2012 \u201cLifetime Achievement Award\u201d at the Nuit de la Glisse\n* 2017 National Sailing Hall of Fame <ref>{{cite web|url=https://nshof.org/inductees/naish-robbie/|title=Robby Naish 2017 Inductee |publisher=Nshof.org |date= |accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* 2019 Hawaii Waterman Hall of Fame Induction\n* Founding Member of the Laureus World Sports Academy\n* 6-time Surfer of the Year (German SURF Magazine)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.naish.com/ Naish] Naish kites, windsurf and surfboard site\n*[http://www.internationalwindsurfing.com/Default.asp?menu=170&parent=165&grandparent=29&newsid=93 International Windsurfing Association biography]\n*[https://www.redbull.com/us-en/athlete/robby-naish Robby Naish Red Bull]\n*[https://quiksilver.com/surf/team/robby-naish.html Robby Naish Quiksilver]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naish, Robert}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American windsurfers]]\n[[Category:American kitesurfers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Male kitesurfers]]\n[[Category:American sportsmen]]\n[[Category:Windsurfing]]\n[[Category:Hydrofoils]]\n[[Category:Kites]]\n[[Category:Kitesurfers]]\n[[Category:Surfing]]\n[[Category:Laureus World Sports Awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{No footnotes|date=September 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=September 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| honorific_prefix     = \n| name                 = Robby Naish\n| honorific_suffix     = \n| image            