\u20131\n|1\n|2014\n|{{Winning percentage|0|1}}\n|-\n|Sugar Bowl\n|4\u20132\n|6\n|2002\n|{{Winning percentage|4|2}}\n|-\n|Sun Bowl\n|0\u20133\n|3\n|1966\n|{{Winning percentage|0|3}}\n|-\n|Tangerine Bowl\n|1\u20130\n|1\n|1977\n|{{Winning percentage|1|0}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Florida State Seminoles bowl game navbox}}\n{{Florida State Seminoles football navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Florida State Seminoles Football}}\n[[Category:Lists of college bowl games by team|Florida State]]\n[[Category:Florida State Seminoles football bowl games|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:GatorBowl1967.jpg|thumb|right|250px|FSU in the 1967 Gator Bowl vs. Penn State]]\nThe [[Florida State Seminoles football]] team competes as part of the NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision (FBS), representing [[Florida State University]] in the [[ACC Atlantic Division|Atlantic Division]] of the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC). Since the establishment of the team in 1902, Florida State has appeared in 49 bowl games, including eighteen combined appearances in the traditional \"big four\" bowl games (the [[Rose Bowl Game|Rose]], [[Sugar Bowl|Sugar]], [[Cotton Bowl Classic|Cotton]], and [[Orange Bowl|Orange]]), eight [[Bowl Championship Series]] game appearances, with two victories in the [[BCS National Championship Game]], and one appearance in the [[College Football Playoff]]. The Seminoles have appeared in ten Orange Bowls, winning five of those games.\n\n[[File:Emerald Bowl, UCLA vs FSU, 2006.jpg|thumb|left|250px|FSU vacated their appearance in the 2006 Emerald Bowl vs. UCLA]]\nFlorida State maintains a record of 28\u201317\u20133 record in bowl games. The Seminoles played in 36 consecutive bowl games from 1982-2017, the longest streak in college football history, although the NCAA doesn't recognize this because their 2006 Emerald Bowl win and appearance were both vacated as a result of the 2007 academic scandal. \n\nFlorida State also owns the record for the most consecutive bowl game victories with 11, between 1985 and 1996, as well as the longest unbeaten streak with a 13\u20130\u20131 record from 1982\u20131996.\n\n==Bowl games==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Florida State Seminoles|#|Date|Bowl|Opponent|Result}}\n|-\n| 1. || November 26, 1903 || Florida Times-Union\u2019s Championship Cup || [[Stetson University|Stetson]] || '''T''' 5\u20135\n|-\n| 2. || January 2, 1950 || [[Cigar Bowl]] || [[Wofford College|Wofford]] || '''W''' 19\u20136\n|-\n| 3. || [[1955 Sun Bowl|January 1, 1955]] || [[Sun Bowl]] || [[UTEP|Texas-El Paso]] || '''L''' 20\u201347\n|-\n| 4. || [[Bluegrass Bowl#1958 Bluegrass Bowl|December 13, 1958]] || [[Bluegrass Bowl]] || [[Oklahoma State Cowboys football|Oklahoma State]] || '''L''' 6\u201315\n|-\n| 5. || January 2, 1965 || [[Gator Bowl]] || [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]] || '''W''' 36\u201319\n|-\n| 6. || [[1966 Sun Bowl|December 24, 1966]] || Sun Bowl || [[University of Wyoming|Wyoming]] || '''L''' 20\u201328\n|-\n| 7. || December 30, 1967 || Gator Bowl || [[Penn State Nittany Lions football|Penn State]] || '''T''' 17\u201317\n|-\n| 8. || [[1968 Peach Bowl|December 30, 1968]] || [[Peach Bowl]] || [[LSU Tigers football|LSU]] || '''L''' 27\u201331\n|-\n| 9. || [[1971 Fiesta Bowl|December 23, 1971]] || [[Fiesta Bowl]] || [[Arizona State Sun Devils football|Arizona State]] || '''L''' 38\u201345\n|-\n| 10. || December 23, 1977 || [[Tangerine Bowl (1947\u201382)|Tangerine Bowl]] || [[Texas Tech Red Raiders football|Texas Tech]] || '''W''' 40\u201317\n|-\n| 11. || [[1980 Orange Bowl|January 1, 1980]] || [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] || Oklahoma || '''L''' 7\u201324\n|-\n| 12. || [[1981 Orange Bowl|January 1, 1981]] || Orange Bowl || Oklahoma || '''L''' 17\u201318\n|-\n| 13. || December 30, 1982 || Gator Bowl || [[West Virginia Mountaineers|West Virginia]] || '''W''' 31\u201312\n|-\n| 14. || [[1983 Peach Bowl|December 30, 1983]] || Peach 